The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and involves linear algebra and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also proposes an improvement on an algorithm, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The reduction from dense subgraph problems suggests a connection to graph theory and algorithms (cs.NA), while the spectral algorithm proposed for certifying random graphs relates to statistical learning (cs.SI).
